name: port_count;
display name: Port Count;
description: Port Count - added so that CauseMos can graph the number of ports in a geographic region. Ports are grouped according to country and locality, and are listed in geographic sequence as shown on the chartlets in the fore part of the volume, following, in general, the coastal trend. The listing of ports in off-lying islands normally interrupts the coastal listing at some convenient place abreast of the island. River ports are listed toward the head of navigation, alternating from bank to bank, except where local considerations make other arrangements more practicable.
In general, ports are listed under the names approved by the U.S. Board on Geographic Names. Alternate or more familiar names, however, are also included in the index, under the same index number. Data source: https://console.cloud.google.com/bigquery?page=table&ref=https:%2F%2Fconsole.cloud.google.com%2Fmarketplace%2Fproduct%2Fnoaa-public%2Fhurricanes&project=capable-arbor-337814&supportedpurview=project&ws=!1m49!1m3!3m2!1sbigquery-public-data!2snoaa_hurricanes!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2snoaa_hurricanes!3shurricanes!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2snoaa_significant_earthquakes!3searthquakes!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2sworldpop!3spopulation_grid_1km!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2sworld_bank_wdi!3sindicators_data!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2susda_nass_agriculture!3scrops!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2snoaa_global_forecast_system!3sNOAA_GFS0P25!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2sgoogle_trends!3stop_rising_terms!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2sgeo_international_ports!3sworld_port_index!1m4!4m3!1sbigquery-public-data!2scovid19_geotab_mobility_impact!3sport_traffic&d=geo_international_ports&p=bigquery-public-data&t=world_port_index;
