unit: years;
unit description: years;

name: SP.DYN.AMRT.FE;
display name: Mortality rate, adult, female (per 1,000 female adults);
description: Adult mortality rate, female, is the probability of dying between the ages of 15 and 60--that is, the probability of a 15-year-old female dying before reaching age 60, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year between those ages.;
unit: per 1,000 female adults;
unit description: per 1,000 female adults;

name: SP.DYN.AMRT.MA;
display name: Mortality rate, adult, male (per 1,000 male adults);
description: Adult mortality rate, male, is the probability of dying between the ages of 15 and 60--that is, the probability of a 15-year-old male dying before reaching age 60, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year between those ages.;
unit: per 1,000 male adults;
unit description: per 1,000 male adults;

name: SP.DYN.IMRT.IN;
display name: Mortality rate, infant (per 1,000 live births);
description: Infant mortality rate is the number of infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 live births in a given year.;
unit: per 1,000 live births;
unit description: per 1,000 live births;

name: SP.DYN.IMRT.FE.IN;
display name: Mortality rate, infant, female (per 1,000 live births);
description: Infant mortality rate, female is the number of female infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 female live births in a given year.;
unit: per 1,000 live births;
unit description: per 1,000 live births;

name: SP.DYN.IMRT.MA.IN;
display name: Mortality rate, infant, male (per 1,000 live births);
description: Infant mortality rate, male is the number of male infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 male live births in a given year.;
unit: per 1,000 live births;
unit description: per 1,000 live births;

