name: SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS;
display name: Labor force participation rate, total (% of total population ages 15-64) (modeled ILO estimate);
description: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15-64 that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period.;
unit: modeled ILO estimate;
unit description: modeled ILO estimate;

name: SL.TLF.ADVN.ZS;
display name: Labor force with advanced education (% of total working-age population with advanced education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with advanced education to the working-age population with advanced education. Advanced education comprises short-cycle tertiary education, a bachelor’s degree or equivalent education level, a master’s degree or equivalent education level, or doctoral degree or equivalent education level according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of total working-age population with advanced education;
unit description: % of total working-age population with advanced education;

name: SL.TLF.ADVN.FE.ZS;
display name: Labor force with advanced education, female (% of female working-age population with advanced education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with advanced education to the working-age population with advanced education. Advanced education comprises short-cycle tertiary education, a bachelor’s degree or equivalent education level, a master’s degree or equivalent education level, or doctoral degree or equivalent education level according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of female working-age population with advanced education;
unit description: % of female working-age population with advanced education;

name: SL.TLF.ADVN.MA.ZS;
display name: Labor force with advanced education, male (% of male working-age population with advanced education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with advanced education to the working-age population with advanced education. Advanced education comprises short-cycle tertiary education, a bachelor’s degree or equivalent education level, a master’s degree or equivalent education level, or doctoral degree or equivalent education level according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of male working-age population with advanced education;
unit description: % of male working-age population with advanced education;

name: SL.TLF.BASC.ZS;
display name: Labor force with basic education (% of total working-age population with basic education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with basic education to the working-age population with basic education. Basic education comprises primary education or lower secondary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of total working-age population with basic education;
unit description: % of total working-age population with basic education;

name: SL.TLF.BASC.FE.ZS;
display name: Labor force with basic education, female (% of female working-age population with basic education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with basic education to the working-age population with basic education. Basic education comprises primary education or lower secondary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of female working-age population with basic education;
unit description: % of female working-age population with basic education;

name: SL.TLF.BASC.MA.ZS;
display name: Labor force with basic education, male (% of male working-age population with basic education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with basic education to the working-age population with basic education. Basic education comprises primary education or lower secondary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of male working-age population with basic education;
unit description: % of male working-age population with basic education;

name: SL.TLF.INTM.ZS;
display name: Labor force with intermediate education (% of total working-age population with intermediate education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with intermediate education to the working-age population with intermediate education. Intermediate education comprises upper secondary or post-secondary non tertiary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of total working-age population with intermediate education;
unit description: % of total working-age population with intermediate education;

name: SL.TLF.INTM.FE.ZS;
display name: Labor force with intermediate education, female (% of female working-age population with intermediate education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with intermediate education to the working-age population with intermediate education. Intermediate education comprises upper secondary or post-secondary non tertiary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of female working-age population with intermediate education;
unit description: % of female working-age population with intermediate education;

name: SL.TLF.INTM.MA.ZS;
display name: Labor force with intermediate education, male (% of male working-age population with intermediate education);
description: The ratio of the labor force with intermediate education to the working-age population with intermediate education. Intermediate education comprises upper secondary or post-secondary non tertiary education according to the International Standard Classification of Education 2011 (ISCED 2011).;
unit: % of male working-age population with intermediate education;
unit description: % of male working-age population with intermediate education;

name: SL.TLF.TOTL.FE.ZS;
display name: Labor force, female (% of total labor force);
description: Female labor force as a percentage of the total show the extent to which women are active in the labor force. Labor force comprises people ages 15 and older who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period.;
unit: % of total labor force;
unit description: % of total labor force;

name: SL.TLF.TOTL.IN;
display name: Labor force, total;
description: Labor force comprises people ages 15 and older who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period. It includes people who are currently employed and people who are unemployed but seeking work as well as first-time job-seekers. Not everyone who works is included, however. Unpaid workers, family workers, and students are often omitted, and some countries do not count members of the armed forces. Labor force size tends to vary during the year as seasonal workers enter and leave.;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SL.TLF.PART.FE.ZS;
display name: Part time employment, female (% of total female employment);
description: Part time employment refers to regular employment in which working time is substantially less than normal. Definitions of part time employment differ by country.;
unit: % of total female employment;
unit description: % of total female employment;

name: SL.TLF.PART.MA.ZS;
display name: Part time employment, male (% of total male employment);
description: Part time employment refers to regular employment in which working time is substantially less than normal. Definitions of part time employment differ by country.;
unit: % of total male employment;
unit description: % of total male employment;

name: SL.TLF.PART.ZS;
display name: Part time employment, total (% of total employment);
description: Part time employment refers to regular employment in which working time is substantially less than normal. Definitions of part time employment differ by country.;
unit: % of total employment;
unit description: % of total employment;

name: SL.TLF.CACT.FM.ZS;
display name: Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate (%) (modeled ILO estimate);
description: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period. Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate is calculated by dividing female labor force participation rate by male labor force participation rate and multiplying by 100.;
unit: modeled ILO estimate;
unit description: modeled ILO estimate;

name: SL.TLF.CACT.FM.NE.ZS;
display name: Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate (%) (national estimate);
description: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period. Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate is calculated by dividing female labor force participation rate by male labor force participation rate and multiplying by 100.;
unit: national estimate;
unit description: national estimate;

name: FD.RES.LIQU.AS.ZS;
display name: Bank liquid reserves to bank assets ratio (%);
description: Ratio of bank liquid reserves to bank assets is the ratio of domestic currency holdings and deposits with the monetary authorities to claims on other governments, nonfinancial public enterprises, the private sector, and other banking institutions.;
unit: %;
unit description: %;

name: FD.AST.PRVT.GD.ZS;
display name: Domestic credit to private sector by banks (% of GDP);
description: Domestic credit to private sector by banks refers to financial resources provided to the private sector by other depository corporations (deposit taking corporations except central banks), such as through loans, purchases of nonequity securities, and trade credits and other accounts receivable, that establish a claim for repayment. For some countries these claims include credit to public enterprises.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: VC.BTL.DETH;
display name: Battle-related deaths (number of people);
description: Battle-related deaths are deaths in battle-related conflicts between warring parties in the conflict dyad (two conflict units that are parties to a conflict). Typically, battle-related deaths occur in warfare involving the armed forces of the warring parties. This includes traditional battlefield fighting, guerrilla activities, and all kinds of bombardments of military units, cities, and villages, etc. The targets are usually the military itself and its installations or state institutions and state representatives, but there is often substantial collateral damage in the form of civilians being killed in crossfire, in indiscriminate bombings, etc. All deaths--military as well as civilian--incurred in such situations, are counted as battle-related deaths.;
unit: number of people;
unit description: number of people;

name: VC.IHR.PSRC.P5;
display name: Intentional homicides (per 100,000 people);
description: Intentional homicides are estimates of unlawful homicides purposely inflicted as a result of domestic disputes, interpersonal violence, violent conflicts over land resources, intergang violence over turf or control, and predatory violence and killing by armed groups. Intentional homicide does not include all intentional killing; the difference is usually in the organization of the killing. Individuals or small groups usually commit homicide, whereas killing in armed conflict is usually committed by fairly cohesive groups of up to several hundred members and is thus usually excluded.;
unit: per 100,000 people;
unit description: per 100,000 people;

name: VC.IHR.PSRC.FE.P5;
display name: Intentional homicides, female (per 100,000 female);
description: Intentional homicides, female are estimates of unlawful female homicides purposely inflicted as a result of domestic disputes, interpersonal violence, violent conflicts over land resources, intergang violence over turf or control, and predatory violence and killing by armed groups. Intentional homicide does not include all intentional killing; the difference is usually in the organization of the killing. Individuals or small groups usually commit homicide, whereas killing in armed conflict is usually committed by fairly cohesive groups of up to several hundred members and is thus usually excluded.;
unit: per 100,000 female;
unit description: per 100,000 female;

name: VC.IHR.PSRC.MA.P5;
display name: Intentional homicides, male (per 100,000 male);
description: Intentional homicides, male are estimates of unlawful male homicides purposely inflicted as a result of domestic disputes, interpersonal violence, violent conflicts over land resources, intergang violence over turf or control, and predatory violence and killing by armed groups. Intentional homicide does not include all intentional killing; the difference is usually in the organization of the killing. Individuals or small groups usually commit homicide, whereas killing in armed conflict is usually committed by fairly cohesive groups of up to several hundred members and is thus usually excluded.;
unit: per 100,000 male;
unit description: per 100,000 male;

name: VC.IDP.NWCV;
display name: Internally displaced persons, new displacement associated with conflict and violence (number of cases);
description: Internally displaced persons are defined according to the 1998 Guiding Principles (http://www.internal-displacement.org/publications/1998/ocha-guiding-principles-on-internal-displacement) as people or groups of people who have been forced or obliged to flee or to leave their homes or places of habitual residence, in particular as a result of armed conflict, or to avoid the effects of armed conflict, situations of generalized violence, violations of human rights, or natural or human-made disasters and who have not crossed an international border. "New Displacement" refers to the number of new cases or incidents of displacement recorded over the specified year, rather than the number of people displaced. This is done because people may have been displaced more than once.;
unit: number of cases;
unit description: number of cases;

name: VC.IDP.NWDS;
display name: Internally displaced persons, new displacement associated with disasters (number of cases);
description: Internally displaced persons are defined according to the 1998 Guiding Principles (http://www.internal-displacement.org/publications/1998/ocha-guiding-principles-on-internal-displacement) as people or groups of people who have been forced or obliged to flee or to leave their homes or places of habitual residence, in particular as a result of armed conflict, or to avoid the effects of armed conflict, situations of generalized violence, violations of human rights, or natural or human-made disasters and who have not crossed an international border. "New Displacement" refers to the number of new cases or incidents of displacement recorded over the specified year, rather than the number of people displaced. This is done because people may have been displaced more than once.;
unit: number of cases;
unit description: number of cases;

name: VC.IDP.TOCV;
display name: Internally displaced persons, total displaced by conflict and violence (number of people);
description: Internally displaced persons are defined according to the 1998 Guiding Principles (http://www.internal-displacement.org/publications/1998/ocha-guiding-principles-on-internal-displacement) as people or groups of people who have been forced or obliged to flee or to leave their homes or places of habitual residence, in particular as a result of armed conflict, or to avoid the effects of armed conflict, situations of generalized violence, violations of human rights, or natural or human-made disasters and who have not crossed an international border. “People displaced” refers to the number of people living in displacement as of the end of each year, and reflects the stock of people displaced at the end of the previous year, plus inflows of new cases arriving over the year as well as births over the year to those displaced, minus outflows which may include returnees, those who settled elsewhere, those who integrated locally, those who travelled over borders, and deaths.;
unit: number of people;
unit description: number of people;

name: FM.LBL.BMNY.GD.ZS;
display name: Broad money (% of GDP);
description: Broad money (IFS line 35L..ZK) is the sum of currency outside banks; demand deposits other than those of the central government; the time, savings, and foreign currency deposits of resident sectors other than the central government; bank and traveler’s checks; and other securities such as certificates of deposit and commercial paper.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: FM.LBL.BMNY.CN;
display name: Broad money (current LCU);
description: Broad money (IFS line 35L..ZK) is the sum of currency outside banks; demand deposits other than those of the central government; the time, savings, and foreign currency deposits of resident sectors other than the central government; bank and traveler’s checks; and other securities such as certificates of deposit and commercial paper.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: FM.LBL.BMNY.ZG;
display name: Broad money growth (annual %);
description: Broad money (IFS line 35L..ZK) is the sum of currency outside banks; demand deposits other than those of the central government; the time, savings, and foreign currency deposits of resident sectors other than the central government; bank and traveler’s checks; and other securities such as certificates of deposit and commercial paper.;
unit: annual %;
unit description: annual %;

name: FM.LBL.BMNY.IR.ZS;
display name: Broad money to total reserves ratio;
description: Broad money (IFS line 35L..ZK) is the sum of currency outside banks; demand deposits other than those of the central government; the time, savings, and foreign currency deposits of resident sectors other than the central government; bank and traveler’s checks; and other securities such as certificates of deposit and commercial paper.;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: FM.AST.CGOV.ZG.M3;
display name: Claims on central government (annual growth as % of broad money);
description: Claims on central government (IFS line 32AN..ZK) include loans to central government institutions net of deposits.;
unit: annual growth as % of broad money;
unit description: annual growth as % of broad money;

name: FM.AST.DOMO.ZG.M3;
display name: Claims on other sectors of the domestic economy (annual growth as % of broad money);
description: Claims on other sectors of the domestic economy (IFS line 32S..ZK) include gross credit from the financial system to households, nonprofit institutions serving households, nonfinancial corporations, state and local governments, and social security funds.;
unit: annual growth as % of broad money;
unit description: annual growth as % of broad money;

name: FM.AST.PRVT.ZG.M3;
display name: Claims on private sector (annual growth as % of broad money);
description: Claims on private sector (IFS line 32D..ZK or 32D..ZF) include gross credit from the financial system to individuals, enterprises, nonfinancial public entities not included under net domestic credit, and financial institutions not included elsewhere.;
unit: annual growth as % of broad money;
unit description: annual growth as % of broad money;

name: FM.AST.PRVT.GD.ZS;
display name: Monetary Sector credit to private sector (% GDP);
description: Domestic credit to private sector refers to financial resources provided to the private sector, such as through loans, purchases of nonequity securities, and trade credits and other accounts receivable, that establish a claim for repayment. For some countries these claims include credit to public enterprises.;
unit: % GDP;
unit description: % GDP;

name: FM.AST.DOMS.CN;
display name: Net domestic credit (current LCU);
description: Net domestic credit is the sum of net claims on the central government and claims on other sectors of the domestic economy (IFS line 32). Data are in current local currency.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: FM.AST.NFRG.CN;
display name: Net foreign assets (current LCU);
description: Net foreign assets are the sum of foreign assets held by monetary authorities and deposit money banks, less their foreign liabilities. Data are in current local currency.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: SH.DTH.COMM.ZS;
display name: Cause of death, by communicable diseases and maternal, prenatal and nutrition conditions (% of total);
description: Cause of death refers to the share of all deaths for all ages by underlying causes. Communicable diseases and maternal, prenatal and nutrition conditions include infectious and parasitic diseases, respiratory infections, and nutritional deficiencies such as underweight and stunting.;
unit: % of total;
unit description: % of total;

name: SH.DTH.INJR.ZS;
display name: Cause of death, by injury (% of total);
description: Cause of death refers to the share of all deaths for all ages by underlying causes. Injuries include unintentional and intentional injuries.;
unit: % of total;
unit description: % of total;

name: SH.DTH.NCOM.ZS;
display name: Cause of death, by non-communicable diseases (% of total);
description: Cause of death refers to the share of all deaths for all ages by underlying causes. Non-communicable diseases include cancer, diabetes mellitus, cardiovascular diseases, digestive diseases, skin diseases, musculoskeletal diseases, and congenital anomalies.;
unit: % of total;
unit description: % of total;

name: SH.DTH.1014;
display name: Number of deaths ages 10-14 years;
description: Number of deaths of adolescents ages 10-14 years;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.1519;
display name: Number of deaths ages 15-19 years;
description: Number of deaths of adolescents ages 15-19 years;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.2024;
display name: Number of deaths ages 20-24 years;
description: Number of deaths of youths ages 20-24 years;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.0509;
display name: Number of deaths ages 5-9 years;
description: Number of deaths of children ages 5-9 years;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.IMRT;
display name: Number of infant deaths;
description: Number of infants dying before reaching one year of age.;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.NMRT;
display name: Number of neonatal deaths;
description: Number of neonates dying before reaching 28 days of age.;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: SH.DTH.MORT;
display name: Number of under-five deaths;
description: Number of children dying before reaching age five.;
unit: NA;
unit description: NA;

name: GC.DOD.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Central government debt, total (% of GDP);
description: Debt is the entire stock of direct government fixed-term contractual obligations to others outstanding on a particular date. It includes domestic and foreign liabilities such as currency and money deposits, securities other than shares, and loans. It is the gross amount of government liabilities reduced by the amount of equity and financial derivatives held by the government. Because debt is a stock rather than a flow, it is measured as of a given date, usually the last day of the fiscal year.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.DOD.TOTL.CN;
display name: Central government debt, total (current LCU);
description: Debt is the entire stock of direct government fixed-term contractual obligations to others outstanding on a particular date. It includes domestic and foreign liabilities such as currency and money deposits, securities other than shares, and loans. It is the gross amount of government liabilities reduced by the amount of equity and financial derivatives held by the government. Because debt is a stock rather than a flow, it is measured as of a given date, usually the last day of the fiscal year.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.XPN.COMP.ZS;
display name: Compensation of employees (% of expense);
description: Compensation of employees consists of all payments in cash, as well as in kind (such as food and housing), to employees in return for services rendered, and government contributions to social insurance schemes such as social security and pensions that provide benefits to employees.;
unit: % of expense;
unit description: % of expense;

name: GC.XPN.COMP.CN;
display name: Compensation of employees (current LCU);
description: Compensation of employees consists of all payments in cash, as well as in kind (such as food and housing), to employees in return for services rendered, and government contributions to social insurance schemes such as social security and pensions that provide benefits to employees.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.TAX.IMPT.ZS;
display name: Customs and other import duties (% of tax revenue);
description: Customs and other import duties are all levies collected on goods that are entering the country or services delivered by nonresidents to residents. They include levies imposed for revenue or protection purposes and determined on a specific or ad valorem basis as long as they are restricted to imported goods or services.;
unit: % of tax revenue;
unit description: % of tax revenue;

name: GC.TAX.IMPT.CN;
display name: Customs and other import duties (current LCU);
description: Customs and other import duties are all levies collected on goods that are entering the country or services delivered by nonresidents to residents. They include levies imposed for revenue or protection purposes and determined on a specific or ad valorem basis as long as they are restricted to imported goods or services.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.XPN.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Expense (% of GDP);
description: Expense is cash payments for operating activities of the government in providing goods and services. It includes compensation of employees (such as wages and salaries), interest and subsidies, grants, social benefits, and other expenses such as rent and dividends.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.XPN.TOTL.CN;
display name: Expense (current LCU);
description: Expense is cash payments for operating activities of the government in providing goods and services. It includes compensation of employees (such as wages and salaries), interest and subsidies, grants, social benefits, and other expenses such as rent and dividends.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.XPN.GSRV.ZS;
display name: Goods and services expense (% of expense);
description: Goods and services include all government payments in exchange for goods and services used for the production of market and nonmarket goods and services. Own-account capital formation is excluded.;
unit: % of expense;
unit description: % of expense;

name: GC.XPN.GSRV.CN;
display name: Goods and services expense (current LCU);
description: Goods and services include all government payments in exchange for goods and services used for the production of market and nonmarket goods and services. Own-account capital formation is excluded.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.REV.GOTR.ZS;
display name: Grants and other revenue (% of revenue);
description: Grants and other revenue include grants from other foreign governments, international organizations, and other government units; interest; dividends; rent; requited, nonrepayable receipts for public purposes (such as fines, administrative fees, and entrepreneurial income from government owner­ship of property); and voluntary, unrequited, nonrepayable receipts other than grants.;
unit: % of revenue;
unit description: % of revenue;

name: GC.REV.GOTR.CN;
display name: Grants and other revenue (current LCU);
description: Grants and other revenue include grants from other foreign governments, international organizations, and other government units; interest; dividends; rent; requited, nonrepayable receipts for public purposes (such as fines, administrative fees, and entrepreneurial income from government owner­ship of property); and voluntary, unrequited, nonrepayable receipts other than grants.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.XPN.INTP.ZS;
display name: Interest payments (% of expense);
description: Interest payments include interest payments on government debt--including long-term bonds, long-term loans, and other debt instruments--to domestic and foreign residents.;
unit: % of expense;
unit description: % of expense;

name: GC.XPN.INTP.RV.ZS;
display name: Interest payments (% of revenue);
description: Interest payments include interest payments on government debt--including long-term bonds, long-term loans, and other debt instruments--to domestic and foreign residents.;
unit: % of revenue;
unit description: % of revenue;

name: GC.XPN.INTP.CN;
display name: Interest payments (current LCU);
description: Interest payments include interest payments on government debt--including long-term bonds, long-term loans, and other debt instruments--to domestic and foreign residents.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.AST.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Net acquisition of financial assets (% of GDP);
description: Net acquisition of government financial assets includes domestic and foreign financial claims, SDRs, and gold bullion held by monetary authorities as a reserve asset. The net acquisition of financial assets should be offset by the net incurrence of liabilities.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.AST.TOTL.CN;
display name: Net acquisition of financial assets (current LCU);
description: Net acquisition of government financial assets includes domestic and foreign financial claims, SDRs, and gold bullion held by monetary authorities as a reserve asset. The net acquisition of financial assets should be offset by the net incurrence of liabilities.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.LBL.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Net incurrence of liabilities, total (% of GDP);
description: Net incurrence of government liabilities includes foreign financing (obtained from nonresidents) and domestic financing (obtained from residents), or the means by which a government provides financial resources to cover a budget deficit or allocates financial resources arising from a budget surplus. The net incurrence of liabilities should be offset by the net acquisition of financial assets.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.LBL.TOTL.CN;
display name: Net incurrence of liabilities, total (current LCU);
description: Net incurrence of government liabilities includes foreign financing (obtained from nonresidents) and domestic financing (obtained from residents), or the means by which a government provides financial resources to cover a budget deficit or allocates financial resources arising from a budget surplus. The net incurrence of liabilities should be offset by the net acquisition of financial assets.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.NFN.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Net investment in nonfinancial assets (% of GDP);
description: Net investment in government nonfinancial assets includes fixed assets, inventories, valuables, and nonproduced assets. Nonfinancial assets are stores of value and provide benefits either through their use in the production of goods and services or in the form of property income and holding gains. Net investment in nonfinancial assets also includes consumption of fixed capital.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.NFN.TOTL.CN;
display name: Net investment in nonfinancial assets (current LCU);
description: Net investment in government nonfinancial assets includes fixed assets, inventories, valuables, and nonproduced assets. Nonfinancial assets are stores of value and provide benefits either through their use in the production of goods and services or in the form of property income and holding gains. Net investment in nonfinancial assets also includes consumption of fixed capital.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.NLD.TOTL.GD.ZS;
display name: Net lending (+) / net borrowing (-) (% of GDP);
description: Net lending (+) / net borrowing (–) equals government revenue minus expense, minus net investment in nonfinancial assets. It is also equal to the net result of transactions in financial assets and liabilities. Net lending/net borrowing is a summary measure indicating the extent to which government is either putting financial resources at the disposal of other sectors in the economy or abroad, or utilizing the financial resources generated by other sectors in the economy or from abroad.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.NLD.TOTL.CN;
display name: Net lending (+) / net borrowing (-) (current LCU);
description: Net lending (+) / net borrowing (–) equals government revenue minus expense, minus net investment in nonfinancial assets. It is also equal to the net result of transactions in financial assets and liabilities. Net lending/net borrowing is a summary measure indicating the extent to which government is either putting financial resources at the disposal of other sectors in the economy or abroad, or utilizing the financial resources generated by other sectors in the economy or from abroad.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.XPN.OTHR.ZS;
display name: Other expense (% of expense);
description: Other expense is spending on dividends, rent, and other miscellaneous expenses, including provision for consumption of fixed capital.;
unit: % of expense;
unit description: % of expense;

name: GC.XPN.OTHR.CN;
display name: Other expense (current LCU);
description: Other expense is spending on dividends, rent, and other miscellaneous expenses, including provision for consumption of fixed capital.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.TAX.OTHR.RV.ZS;
display name: Other taxes (% of revenue);
description: Other taxes include employer payroll or labor taxes, taxes on property, and taxes not allocable to other categories, such as penalties for late payment or nonpayment of taxes.;
unit: % of revenue;
unit description: % of revenue;

name: GC.TAX.OTHR.CN;
display name: Other taxes (current LCU);
description: Other taxes include employer payroll or labor taxes, taxes on property, and taxes not allocable to other categories, such as penalties for late payment or nonpayment of taxes.;
unit: current LCU;
unit description: current LCU;

name: GC.REV.XGRT.GD.ZS;
display name: Revenue, excluding grants (% of GDP);
description: Revenue is cash receipts from taxes, social contributions, and other revenues such as fines, fees, rent, and income from property or sales. Grants are also considered as revenue but are excluded here.;
unit: % of GDP;
unit description: % of GDP;

name: GC.REV.XGRT.CN;
